"""
main.py — Corrective RAG agent for NovAtel documentation Q&A + uploaded log Q&A.

Fixes applied vs previous version:
  1. _build_event_index ITDETECTSTATUS block — rewrote to use corrected
     decode_itdetectstatus() return structure (entries list, not jammer_status etc.)
  2. _build_event_index tracking — removed tracking_lt4_sats (belongs to AUX4,
     not RXSTATUS); replaced with tracking_degraded / tracking_critical from AUX4.
  3. Event index keys — removed dead itdetect_jamming / itdetect_spoofing keys;
     unified under itdetect_interference.
  4. analyze_events docstring + event keys — aligned tracking_degraded /
     tracking_critical with event index keys.
  5. query_log freq search — fixed to search MHz (not Hz) to match ITDETECTSTATUS
     fields_raw which stores center_freq_mhz as a float in MHz.
  6. _AGENT_SYSTEM_PROMPT — updated event type list to remove stale keys.
  7. _current_session — replaced module-level mutable dict with contextvars.ContextVar
     for async-safe per-request session isolation.
  8. _normalize_freq_search — removed (dead code, never called).
  9. decode_rxstatus — spoofing=bit9, jamming=bit15 (corrected from bit26/bit28).
 10. decode_itdetectstatus — full rewrite to match actual log format (num_entries +
     repeated 9-field blocks; STATISTICALANALYSIS params are reserved).
 11. _merge_jamming_events — new helper that merges RXSTATUS + ITDETECTSTATUS events
     sharing the same (week, seconds) timestamp into a single entry, so same-second
     events are never double-counted.
 12. analyze_events jamming/spoofing — now returns merged event list with sources[],
     rxstatus_bits[], itdetect_entries[] per entry instead of two separate lists.
 13. query_log limit=None — None means return ALL matching records (no truncation).
     A warning field is added only when the caller explicitly passes a limit and
     results are truncated. Agents should omit limit for min/max/aggregate queries.
 14. query_log field_stats — server-side min/max computed over ALL matching records
     before any capping. Each numeric field position gets {min, max, min_record,
     max_record} so the agent never needs to scan records[] for aggregate answers.
     This is immune to _cap_tool_response trimming because scalars are never trimmed.
 15. _cap_tool_response — now sets truncated=True and adds a warning when it trims
     the records[] list, so the agent always knows when it has a partial record set.
"""

